Translation of clean data labels:

The clean database, after the processes listed in "1 - Pre-processing of raw data from police reports" and "2 - Pre-processing of temporal tabular data", presents the labels in Portuguese listed below, but to facilitate replication for future research, the mapping / translation of each label into English is recorded below.

Obs: CRB means "Crime Registered in Bulletin";
Obs: Variables with "count" refer to the results of counting a crime in a specific year and month;

quant_ameaca_crb  -   threat count;
quant_lesao_corporal_crb  - bodily injury count;
quant_roubo_crb - assault count;
quant_furto_crb - theft count;
quant_injuria_crb - injury count;
quant_outros_fatos_atipicos_crb - count of other atypical facts;
quant_homicidios_crb  - current month's homicide count;
quant_lesao_no_transito_crb - traffic injury count;
quant_calunia_crb - slander count;
quant_difamacao_crb - defamation count;
quant_vias_de_fato_crb  - fight count;
quant_estelionato_crb - count of stelionate;
quant_dano_no_transito_crb  - traffic damage count;
quant_abandono_do_lar_crb - home abandonment count;
quant_conflitos_familiares_crb  - counting family conflicts;
quant_dano_crb  - damage count;
quant_apropriacao_indebita_crb  - count of indefinite appropriation;
quant_trafico_de_drogas_crb - drug trafficking count;
quant_dano_civil_crb  -  civil damage count;
quant_assistencia_social_crb  - welfare count;
quant_roubo_de_veiculo_crb  - vehicle theft count;
quant_poluicao_sonora_crb  -  noise pollution count;
quant_agressao_fisica_crb - physical aggression count;
quant_desobediencia_crb - disobedience count;
quant_receptacao_crb  - reception count;
quant_estupro_crb - rape count;
quant_fuga_do_lar_crb - home escape count;
quant_desaparecimento_de_pessoa_crb - count of person disappearance;
quant_tentativa_de_homicidio_crb  - attempted murder count;
quant_conflitos_vicinais_crb  - count of vicinal conflicts;
quant_conflitos_conjugais_crb - marital conflict count;
quant_desacato_crb  - contempt count;
quant_estupro_de_vulneravel_crb - vulnerable rape count;
quant_outras_fraudes_crb  - count of other scams;
quant_perturbacoes_da_tranquilidade_crb -  tranquility disturbance count;
bairro_crb (metadata)  - neighborhood;
ano_crb (metadata) - year as number;
mes_num_crb - month as number;

Class - Binary classification, 
      1 represents the occurrence of homicide in the following month; and
      0 represents the non-occurrence of homicide in the following month.

meta_mes_crb  - month as text;
meta_ano  - year as text;
meta_bairro - neighborhood name (removed for confidentiality).
